description*.en: "Linear Electric Linear Current Density" is the electric current per unit length. Electric current, $I$, through a curve $C$ is defined as $I = \int_C J _s \times e_n$, where $e_n$ is a unit vector perpendicular to the surface and line vector element, and $dr$ is the differential of position vector $r$.
